meanings.meaning: 3. to go (well, badly, etc.); to proceed; to turn out; to get along あなたのおかげで仕事がうまく行きました。Thanks to you, the job went well.

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb

meanings.meaning: 6. to stream; to flow

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 7. to die; to pass away usu. written as 逝く

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 8. to reach (a stage, extent, age, etc.); to get to; to go (so far as ...)

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 9. to reach (of information, instructions, wind, etc.); to arrive

meanings.type: Auxiliary verb, Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class
meanings.meaning: 10. to continue ...; to go on ...; to (progress) steadily; to gradually ...; to progressively ... Usually written using kana alone, after the -te form of a verb; い sometimes omitted in casual speechその音はだんだん小さくなっていった。The sound grew fainter and fainter.

meanings.type: Godan verb - Iku/Yuku special class, Intransitive verb
meanings.meaning: 11. to have an orgasm; to come; to cum Usually written using kana alone, Colloquial, oft. written as イク
